    <bioghist>Nathan C. Putnam (died 1887) was a merchant in Milan, Mich., and served in Co. K, 1st Michigan Cavalry during the Civil War. His son Alfred E. Putnam married Alice McNeill.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Family portraits, including one of Nathan C. Putnam in uniform. The collection also includes descriptions of the photos and an article about Putnam by Martha Churchill. There are also portraits of McNeill family members with accompanying biographical information, and scanned copies of photos of Hinsdale and McNeill family members.</scopecontent>
